begin_memory_text: We talked about where we're from and what it's like where we're at; at first we talked about fires and whether she still had them in Southern California, and I talked about all the smoke we had in the Pacific Northwest fairly recently and how bad it was.
middle_memory_text: We talked about my town and the schools and what it was like growing up and what it was like for her and the schools there and so on, and we talked about different cultures and food, like Peruvian food and ceviche, and I told her about pupusas, which is a type of Salvadoran food I've had at a restaurant in Olympia when I was living there.
end_memory_text: We talked about what I studied in college and grad school, and we talked about what she's studying in college, and we also talked about coding and some computer stuff as well. We talked some about the weather as well where we've living and I talked a bit about a couple professors I've had who've ridden their bikes to campus.
rest_of_day_open: I need to finish hauling and stacking a bunch of firewood, so that will take a lot of my time. I also should do some work to make some money. I'll probably sign up for a new Python class and start working on that, which will be interesting. I'll probably hang out with some friends online in the evenings, and maybe talk to a friend or two on the phone, which will be nice.
critical_positive: I think we got along well and had a lot in common; it was fun talking with her. We also had some stuff to compare and contrast. I think the conversation also went smoothly in terms of turn-taking and so on. She was really friendly, polite, and nice, and I hope I was as well.
critical_negative: I felt a little bit bad about abruptly stopping the conversation and I hope I didn't seem rude, but I do have a bunch to get done today. Maybe I could have asked more questions about her and talked less about myself, but really I think it was pretty equal. I don't think there wasn't a lot that didn't work well.
